<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-20T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-20T10:00:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/24969:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="from">Cole</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-20T16:00:00+01:00">October 20, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 20—2:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>701. From Murphy for Atherton. For Leahy. Admiral Darlan arrived at
                                Oran this morning en route to Dakar for an inspection trip said to
                                be pending for the last 2 months. He is expected in Algiers on his
                                return in about 1 week stopping over for about 2 days as the guest
                                of General Juin commanding in North Africa.</p>
                            <p>I promised to inquire discreetly whether American specialists might
                                have helpful suggestions to offer regarding treatment of
                                poliomyelitis. Could possibly Admiral McIntire<note n="98" xml:id="d401fn98">Vice Adm. Ross T. McIntire, White House
                                    physician.</note> cable me confidentially anything that might be
                                useful. [Murphy.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>